{"title": "Yohei Matsumoto\n", "url": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yohei_Matsumoto", "tags": ["Category:1973 births", "Category:21st-century Japanese politicians", "Category:Japanese politician, 1970s birth stubs", "Category:Keio University alumni", "Category:Koizumi Children", "Category:Liberal Democratic Party (Japan) politicians", "Category:Living people", "Category:Members of the House of Representatives (Japan)", "Category:Nanjing Massacre deniers", "Category:People from Setagaya", "Category:Short description matches Wikidata"], "text": "Yohei Matsumoto (\u677e\u672c \u6d0b\u5e73, Matsumoto Y\u014dhei, born 1973) is a Japanese politician of the Liberal Democratic Party, a member of the House of Representatives in the Diet (national legislature). A native of Setagaya, Tokyo and graduate of Keio University, he worked at Sanwa Bank, (now part of The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ) from 1996 to 2003. He was elected to the House of Representatives for the first time in 2005 after an unsuccessful run in 2003.\n\nRight-wing positions\nHe was a supporter of right-wing filmmaker Satoru Mizushima's 2007 revisionist film The Truth about Nanjing, which denied that the Nanking Massacre ever occurred.\n\nReferences\nExternal links\nOfficial website in Japanese."}